[1] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Mon 4 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=469441>

At least 123 new cases of cholera were recorded over the last 4 days
at Lubango's Central Hospital, in Angola's southern Huila province, a
health source announced.
Feliz Januario, head of the Department of Public Health, said this is
because people are ignoring prevention measures. However, he said no
deaths were recorded in the mentioned period. Since the beginning of
the outbreak on 11 Apr 2006, the disease has killed 74 people in the
region, out of 944 cases recorded.
--
