[7] Cholera - Liberia
Date: Wed 23 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC Monitoring Africa [edited]
<http://www.redorbit.com/news/health/628228/nine_dead_50_hospitalized_in_southwest_liberia_cholera_outbreak/index.html?source=r_health>

A cholera outbreak has killed 9 persons in several parts of the
country. The Ministry of Health and Social Welfare said the disease
has killed 4 persons in Grand Bassa County, one in Margibi County, 3
in Monrovia, and one in Clay Ashland, Bomi County [all in
southwestern Liberia]. Acting Deputy Health Minister Dr. Moses Peewu
told Star Radio about 50 people are being treated for cholera at the
national referral hospital, the John F. Kennedy Medical Hospital.
--
