[8] Cholera - China (Hong Hong SAR)
Date: Fri 1 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News.gov.hk [edited]
<http://news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/060901/html/060901en05003.htm>

The Center for Health Protection has confirmed the 1st cholera case
of the year [2006], involving a 29-year-old man who lived on the
Mainland and worked in Hong Kong during the incubation period. He is
in stable condition in Princess Margaret Hospital.
His symptoms developed on 28 Aug 2006, and tests found _Vibrio
cholerae_. The strain was identified as serotype Ogawa.
His family members did not have symptoms. Investigations are underway.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
